Dear Bedrock Consumers,

As part of our ongoing effort to expand the approved foundation model catalogue for the organisation, we are pleased to confirm that the following models have been assessed, approved, and are scheduled for enablement across Bedrock-provisioned accounts.

— Approved Models —

Amazon Nova 2 Class:
• Nova 2 Lite (amazon.nova-2-lite-v1:0) — Lightweight model with reasoning capabilities
• Nova 2 Sonic (amazon.nova-2-sonic-v1:0) — Audio/multimodal capabilities

Anthropic Claude 4.6 Class:
• Claude Sonnet 4.6 (anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6) — Balanced performance for everyday workloads
• Claude Opus 4.6 (anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1) — Most capable model for complex reasoning and agentic tasks

— Enablement Schedule —

• Non-Production (NPE) Accounts: <NPE Date>
• Production Accounts: <Prod Date>

— Governance & Access Details —

1. IAM Access: Namespace roles using wildcard patterns (anthropic.claude-*, amazon.nova-*) in allowed_foundation_model_ids will automatically have access to the new models. No Terraform or IAM policy changes required for existing namespaces.

2. Anthropic Use Case Form: A one-time use case submission to Anthropic is required per AWS account. This has been handled as part of the enablement activity.

3. AWS Marketplace Subscription: Third-party models (Anthropic) require a marketplace subscription which is created automatically on first invocation. The necessary aws-marketplace:Subscribe and aws-marketplace:ViewSubscriptions permissions are included in the namespace roles.

4. bedrock:InvokeTool (Nova System Tools): The Nova 2 models support built-in system tools — Web Grounding (live internet search) and Code Interpreter (Python code execution). The bedrock:InvokeTool permission is NOT granted by default as these capabilities cross a security boundary. Teams requiring this functionality must complete a risk assessment and request enablement at the namespace level.

— Action Required —

No action is required for standard model invocation. If your team needs access to Nova system tools (InvokeTool), please raise a request referencing this change.

For any questions or additional namespace access requirements, please reach out to the platform team.

